<paragraph id="8BCCE301227AFFA9A9C516DBFED8AAD9" blockId="3.[171,1230,1536,1851]" lastBlockId="5.[174,1233,186,341]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="246" pageId="3" pageNumber="244">
Diagnosis. This species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227AFFAFABAB16DAFC8CAC96" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[654,790,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227AFFAFABAB16DAFC8CAC96" box="[654,790,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="244">P. clypeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227AFFAFAACF16DBFE1BACF7" author="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P. &amp; Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D." pageId="3" pageNumber="244" pagination="19 - 44" refId="ref4238" refString="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P., Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. 1990. Sur quelques especes de Platycheirus (Diptera, Syrphidae) nouvelles ou meconnues. Dipterists Digest, 5, 19 - 44." type="journal article" year="1990">Speight &amp; Goeldlin de Tiefenau, 1990</bibRefCitation>
; Bartsh et al., 2009). This group can be recognized by the entirely black antenna, orange-brown markings on the abdominal tergites, facial prominence and upper mouth-edge projecting anteriorly no further than the frontal prominence, male fore tibiae widening progressively from base to apex (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227AFFAFAB95175BFBE7AD17" author="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P. &amp; Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D." box="[688,1149,1824,1851]" pageId="3" pageNumber="244" pagination="19 - 44" refId="ref4238" refString="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P., Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. 1990. Sur quelques especes de Platycheirus (Diptera, Syrphidae) nouvelles ou meconnues. Dipterists Digest, 5, 19 - 44." type="journal article" year="1990">Speight &amp; Goeldlin de Tiefenau, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Male differs from similar species (
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8AB2A139BFC3BA9D6" authority="(Zetterstedt, 1843)" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[527,929,991,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8AB2A139BFD2BA9D5" box="[527,689,992,1017]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. angustatus</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8AA96139BFE4EAE36" authority="Goeldlin, Maibach &amp; Speight, 1990" authorityName="Goeldlin, Maibach &amp; Speight" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="europaeus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8AA96139BFBD4A9D5" box="[947,1102,992,1017]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. europaeus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227DFFA8AD7E13A4FE4EAE36" author="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P. &amp; Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D." pageId="4" pageNumber="245" pagination="19 - 44" refId="ref4238" refString="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P., Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. 1990. Sur quelques especes de Platycheirus (Diptera, Syrphidae) nouvelles ou meconnues. Dipterists Digest, 5, 19 - 44." type="journal article" year="1990">Goeldlin, Maibach &amp; Speight, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8AB36147BFBF6AE36" authority="Goeldlin, Maibach &amp; Speight, 1990" authorityName="Goeldlin, Maibach &amp; Speight" authorityYear="1990" box="[531,1132,1023,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramsarensis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8AB36147BFD27AE35" box="[531,701,1024,1049]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. ramsarensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227DFFA8ABE31384FBF6AE36" author="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P. &amp; Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D." box="[710,1132,1023,1050]" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" pagination="19 - 44" refId="ref4238" refString="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P., Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. 1990. Sur quelques especes de Platycheirus (Diptera, Syrphidae) nouvelles ou meconnues. Dipterists Digest, 5, 19 - 44." type="journal article" year="1990">Goeldlin, Maibach &amp; Speight, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) by the underside of the basotarsomere of the fore tarsus with a straight, pale central furrow, sometimes ending in a small round pit containing a black mark (fig. 18) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8AD03143BFB58AE75" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[1062,1218,1088,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8AD03143BFB58AE75" box="[1062,1218,1088,1113]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. angustatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A983141BFEA5AE55" authorityName="Goeldlin, Maibach &amp; Speight" authorityYear="1990" box="[166,319,1120,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="europaeus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A983141BFEA5AE55" box="[166,319,1120,1145]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. europaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A8A7141BFDB4AE55" authorityName="Goeldlin, Maibach &amp; Speight" authorityYear="1990" box="[386,558,1120,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramsarensis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A8A7141BFDB4AE55" box="[386,558,1120,1145]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. ramsarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the underside of the basotarsomere of the fore tarsus with a V-shaped pale furrow), the distal half of all segments of the fore tarsus without a brown/black maculae ventrally (fig. 18) (in the aforementioned species, the distal half of the segments 2–3 of the fore tarsus often with a brown/black maculae ventrally). From similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A825149BFDC7AED6" authority="Mutin, 1999" authorityName="Mutin" authorityYear="1999" box="[256,605,1247,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magadanensis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A825149BFE59AED5" box="[256,451,1247,1273]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. magadanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227DFFA8A8EE14A4FDC7AED6" author="Mutin, V. A. &amp; Barkalov, A. V." box="[459,605,1247,1274]" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" pagination="342 - 500" refId="ref4594" refString="Mutin, V. A. &amp; Barkalov, A. V. 1999. Fam. Syrphidae - hoverflies. In: Lehr, P. A., ed. Key to the insects of Russian Far East. Vol. 6 (Diptera and Siphonaptera), pt. 1. Dalnauka Publishing House, Vladivostok, 342 - 500 [In Russian]." type="book chapter" year="1999">Mutin, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by the pale furrow on the underside of the basotarsomere of the fore tarsus starting at its base and ending in a pit that is more readily visible than the furrow (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A8D6155BFD23AF15" authorityName="Mutin" authorityYear="1999" box="[499,697,1311,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magadanensis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A8D6155BFD23AF15" box="[499,697,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. magadanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the underside of the basotarsomere of the fore tarsus with a relatively broad, shining furrow covering the central third of its length); posterior side of the fore femur (in addition to the bent, white seta) with several bent hairs (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A9F515FBFE08AFB5" authorityName="Mutin" authorityYear="1999" box="[208,402,1407,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magadanensis">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A9F515FBFE08AFB5" box="[208,402,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. magadanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, posterior side of the fore femur (except for the bent, white seta) with only straight hairs) (Bartsh et al., 2009). 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8AB8115E4FC07AF95" authorityName="Goeldlin, Maibach and Speight" authorityYear="1990" box="[676,925,1439,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occultus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8AB8115E4FC07AF95" box="[676,925,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">Platycheirus occultus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A98315BBFE74AFF6" authority="(Meigen, 1822)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[166,494,1471,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A98315BBFEAAAFF5" box="[166,304,1471,1497]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. clypeatus</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1822)
</taxonomicName>
by the pale furrow on the underside of the basotarsomere of the fore tarsus ending already in the middle of the segment (sometimes we see only a pit at the centre of the segment, as on fig. 18) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8AB8E167BFCAEAC35" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[683,820,1535,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8AB8E167BFCAEAC35" box="[683,820,1535,1561]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. clypeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the pale furrow on the underside of the basotarsomere of the fore tarsus ending near the apex), and at least the basal quarter of the posterior side of the fore femur is black (fig. 17) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8AA62163BFC55AC75" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[839,975,1599,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8AA62163BFC55AC75" box="[839,975,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. clypeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the fore femur more or less entirely yellow, at most slightly black at base) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227DFFA8AA1B1624FF7BACB6" author="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P. &amp; Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D." pageId="4" pageNumber="245" pagination="19 - 44" refId="ref4238" refString="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P., Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. 1990. Sur quelques especes de Platycheirus (Diptera, Syrphidae) nouvelles ou meconnues. Dipterists Digest, 5, 19 - 44." type="journal article" year="1990">Speight &amp; Goeldlin de Tiefenau, 1990</bibRefCitation>
; Bartsh et al., 2009). From similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8AB5216FBFC58ACB6" authority="Goeldlin, 1974" authorityName="Goeldlin" authorityYear="1974" box="[631,962,1663,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipes">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8AB5216FBFC95ACB5" box="[631,783,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. angustipes</emphasis>
Goeldlin, 1974
</taxonomicName>
it can be separated by the distal half of all segments of the fore tarsus without a brown/black maculae ventrally (fig. 18) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A80816BBFE59ACF5" authorityName="Goeldlin" authorityYear="1974" box="[301,451,1728,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipes">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A80816BBFE59ACF5" box="[301,451,1728,1753]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. angustipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the distal half of all segments of the fore tarsus with a large brown/ black maculae ventrally), the fore femur is black/dark brown for less than the half of length (fig. 17) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A80A177BFE5FAD35" authorityName="Goeldlin" authorityYear="1974" box="[303,453,1792,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipes">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A80A177BFE5FAD35" box="[303,453,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. angustipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the fore femur is black/dark brown for 3/4 of length), and surstyli entirely pale-haired (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A8E5175BFDC3AD15" authorityName="Goeldlin" authorityYear="1974" box="[448,601,1824,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipes">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A8E5175BFDC3AD15" box="[448,601,1824,1849]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">P. angustipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the base of surstyli often with the long black bristly hairs mixed with the pale yellow bristly hairs) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227CFFA9ABF010C1FB0EAAF9" author="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P. &amp; Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D." box="[725,1172,186,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="246" pagination="19 - 44" refId="ref4238" refString="Goeldlin de Tiefenau, P., Maibach, A. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. 1990. Sur quelques especes de Platycheirus (Diptera, Syrphidae) nouvelles ou meconnues. Dipterists Digest, 5, 19 - 44." type="journal article" year="1990">Speight &amp; Goeldlin de Tiefenau, 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227CFFA9ADBA10C1FEADAAD9" author="Van Veen, M. P." pageId="5" pageNumber="246" pagination="1 - 248" refId="ref5309" refString="Van Veen, M. P. 2010. Hoverflies of Northwest Europe. Identification keys to the Syrphidae. Second edition. KNNV Publishing, Utrecht, 1 - 248." type="book chapter" year="2010">
<collectingRegion id="49B72DE3227CFFA9ADBA10C1FB4BAAF9" box="[1183,1233,186,213]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="5" pageNumber="246">Van</collectingRegion>
Veen, 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0CB389227DFFA8A98A1311FE99A999" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454745" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6454745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454745/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" startId="4.[175,214,874,896]" targetBox="[219,1171,174,850]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BCCE301227DFFA8A98A1311FE99A999" blockId="4.[174,1225,874,949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">
Figs 15–18. Male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227DFFA8A8491311FDA8A953" authorityName="Goeldlin, Maibach and Speight" authorityYear="1990" box="[364,562,874,895]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occultus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227DFFA8A8491311FDA8A953" box="[364,562,874,895]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">Platycheirus occultus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 15 — habitus, dorsal view; 16 — head and thorax, anterolateral view; 17 — head, frontal view; 18 — left fore tarsus, ventral view (arrow shows the pit at the center of the basotarsomere).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCCE301227CFFA9A9C61081FCCBAB79" blockId="5.[174,1233,186,341]" pageId="5" pageNumber="246">
Note. The biotope where the specimen was found is corresponding with ones of cluster B (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227CFFA9A8041161FE52AB19" author="Reemer, M." box="[289,456,282,309]" pageId="5" pageNumber="246" pagination="139 - 148" refId="ref4913" refString="Reemer, M. 2000. Hoverflies in the Pripyatskij National Park in southern Belarus (Diptera, Syrphidae). Volucella, 5, 139 - 148." type="journal article" year="2000">Reemer, 2000</bibRefCitation>
), this is the highest part of Irpin River floodplain near mixed forest consisting mainly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227CFFA9A8861141FD99AB78" box="[419,515,314,340]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227CFFA9A8861141FD99AB78" box="[419,515,314,340]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="246">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227CFFA9AB351141FDCBAB7F" box="[528,593,314,339]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227CFFA9AB351141FDCBAB7F" box="[528,593,314,339]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="246">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227CFFA9AB7B1141FD3FAB78" box="[606,677,314,340]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Padus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227CFFA9AB7B1141FD3FAB78" box="[606,677,314,340]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="246">Padus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227CFFA9ABFA1141FCD0AB78" box="[735,842,314,340]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227CFFA9ABFA1141FCD0AB78" box="[735,842,314,340]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="246">Carpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
